headline: U.K. Merger Watchdog Open to Remedies as Synopsys’ Bid for Ansys Faces In-Depth Probe
summary: The U.K. Competition and Markets Authority said it would launch an in-depth probe into Synopsys’ $35 billion acquisition of Ansys, unless the chip-sector companies can offer a deal that eases the regulator’s concerns.
